Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

This soccer database comes from Kaggle and is well suited for data analysis and machine learning. It contains data for soccer matches, players, and teams from several European countries from 2008 to 2016. This dataset is quite extensive.

Question(s) for Analysis¶

  • Which teams are the top performers overall from 2008 to 2016?
  • Which league had the most goals scored per season?
  • Is there any advantage in playing matches at home?
  • which teams are the top performers at home and in away matches?
  • Which teams had the most wins in a single season?
  • Which teams improved the most over the time period?
  • What are the attributes of the top teams?
  • what are the attributes of the top players in 2016? and Does age play a factor in that?

In [27]:
# Adding winner column with winner team name or "Draw"
conditions_list = [
    df_Match_sub['home_team_goal'] > df_Match_sub['away_team_goal'],
    df_Match_sub['home_team_goal'] < df_Match_sub['away_team_goal'],
    df_Match_sub['home_team_goal'] == df_Match_sub['away_team_goal']]
return_list = [df_Match_sub['home_team_name'], df_Match_sub['away_team_name'], 'Draw']
df_Match_sub['winner'] = np.select(conditions_list, return_list)
In [28]:
# Adding loser column with loser team name or "Draw"
conditions_list = [
    df_Match_sub['home_team_goal'] > df_Match_sub['away_team_goal'],
    df_Match_sub['home_team_goal'] < df_Match_sub['away_team_goal'],
    df_Match_sub['home_team_goal'] == df_Match_sub['away_team_goal']]
return_list = [df_Match_sub['away_team_name'], df_Match_sub['home_team_name'], 'Draw']
df_Match_sub['loser'] = np.select(conditions_list, return_list)

Summary¶

In this Section we did the following:

  • Merged the df_League and df_Country dataframes so we know which league belongs to which country.
  • Deleted unnecessary columns in df_Match
  • Created df_Match_sub a sub dataframe with the columns we are interested
  • Fixed some datatypes like date and birthday
  • Merged df_Match_sub with df_Team so we can see the name of the teams in every row, so we can understand who is playing at home or away, and who is the winner
  • Merged it also with df_League so we can see to which league every match belongs to
  • Added to 'total_goals' column to df_Match_sub
  • Added 'winner' and 'loser' columns to df_Match_sub with the name of the teams to make it easier for exploring later
  • Merged df_Team_Attributes with df_Team so we can get the name of the teams in rows, better then dealing with API IDs
  • Merged df_Player_Attributes with df_Player in the same manner so we know each row of stats belongs to which player by getting their name in a new column
  • Checked for any missing or duplicated data through all dataframes and we dealed with them.

Conclusions¶

Results:¶

1. We found that top 10 teams that performed well during this period were:¶

  • FC Barcelona
  • Real Madrid CF
  • Celtic
  • FC Bayern Munich
  • Manchester United
  • Juventus
  • SL Benfica
  • FC Porto
  • Ajax
  • FC Basel
    They won the most matches in their respective leagues during 2008-2016

2. The league with the max total goals scored per season is:¶

Spain LIGA BBVA

3. Is there any advantage in playing matches at home?¶

We found that there is a huge advantage in playing at home, in most of the matches we found that home team winners are more than home team losers, specially in spain, Italy and England. there is no data to see the attributes of this advantage, but we know that it's present and if you are betting, your chances are better if you bet on the home team!

4. which teams are the top performers at home and in away matches?¶

Top 10 performs at their home plays:

  • FC Barcelona
  • Real Madrid CF
  • Celtic
  • Manchester United
  • Manchester City
  • FC Bayern Munich
  • Juventus
  • PSV
  • FC Basel
  • Atlético Madrid

Top 10 performs at away matches:

  • FC Barcelona
  • Real Madrid CF
  • Celtic
  • FC Bayern Munich
  • Juventus
  • SL Benfica
  • FC Porto
  • Ajax
  • FC Basel
  • Manchester United

5. Which teams had the most wins in a single season?¶

Juventus in 2013/2014 season had the most number of wins in a single season during 2008-2016 period, but we see that FC Barcelona and Real Madrid CF did it through out many different seasons!

6. What teams improved the most over the time period?¶

Here are the top 10 sorted:

  • Paris Saint-Germain
  • Atlético Madrid
  • Borussia Mönchengladbach
  • AS Saint-Étienne

  • Aberdeen

While the teams the got worse during this period:

7. The attributes of the top teams:¶

These are the dominant attributes found in the top 50 teams:

Build Up Play Speed Class : Balanced Build Up Play Dribbling Class : Little Build Up Play Passing Class: Mixed Build Up Play Positioning Class: Organized Chance Creation Passing Class : Normal Chance Creation Crossing Class: Normal Chance Creation Shooting Class: Normal Chance Creation Positioning Class: Organized Defense Pressure Class: Medium Defense Aggression Class : Press Defense Team Width Class: Normal Defense Defender Line Class: Cover

8. what are the attributes of the top players in 2016? and Does age play a factor in that?¶

By selecting a group of 50 players that were the top players in 2016 and their age distribution, we found that generally top players are a little older, there is also a general positive correlation with age and overall ratings, it takes experience and training (hence spending more time at the game) to reach the top! We also found that there is a positive correlation between overall ratings and potential of a player, and the same thing between heights and weights of players, which is logical, because physique is really important in this game. When analysing the correlation for heading accuracy, we found that it has a positive correlation with height and jumping. Also Most players with a good finishing can take good penalities because there is a positive correlation between the two.

Limitations:¶

  1. Not clear documentaions about the data. we don't know what some columns represent
  2. We don't have the postitions of players, because we can't comprare defenders to attackers etc ( we can do deeper analysis of players if we had it.
  3. No transfer market data, So we can get the updated player for each team each season
